magazine catch. Recoil-operated.

08:21.840 --> 08:22.840
19 rounds.

08:22.920 --> 08:24.160
<i> Yes, James!</i>

08:24.880 --> 08:27.000
Frodo, call the police.

08:28.320 --> 08:29.360
Ow!

08:32.840 --> 08:33.760
Frodo!

08:33.840 --> 08:36.520
Call the police, you fucking moron!

08:43.200 --> 08:45.000
Told you we had a toilet.

08:46.720 --> 08:49.680
Let me out!
Let me out now!

08:50.680 --> 08:52.120
Frodo!

08:52.600 --> 08:54.120
I don't like my life.

08:55.160 --> 08:56.120
So, do something.

08:57.400 --> 08:58.480
Frodo!

09:13.200 --> 09:14.200
Frodo!

09:15.680 --> 09:16.680
What was that?

09:19.080 --> 09:20.440
Nice one, Frodo.

09:27.000 --> 09:29.480
I'm just saying, it's a bit of a jump,
that's all.

09:30.120 --> 09:31.160
What is? Well, it's weird.

09:35.000 --> 09:35.880
It is.

09:36.920 --> 09:40.120
They steal a car
and he has a knife, sure, but...

09:41.040 --> 09:42.120
why would they kill someone?

09:43.160 --> 09:45.720
Well, he's had the knife
since he was 13 years old.

09:45.800 --> 09:47.600
I had an air rifle when I was ten.

09:50.120 --> 09:51.880
Nearly blinded my sister.

09:57.280 --> 09:58.440
That's interesting.

09:59.200 --> 10:00.240
What?

10:02.080 --> 10:04.280
<i> Things had started to get</i>
<i>slightly out of hand.</i>

10:04.360 --> 10:07.680
I'm going to get you arrested,
and then I'm going to sue you!

10:07.760 --> 10:08.760
All of you!

10:08.840 --> 10:09.960
Shut up!

10:10.520 --> 10:12.160
<i> We needed to get out of there.</i>

10:12.240 --> 10:13.440
-Yeah.

10:13.520 --> 10:16.160
Is that your actual name?
Like, your birth name?

10:16.240 --> 10:17.160
Yeah.

10:18.040 --> 10:20.000
Listen, Frodo, we've got
to get back on the road.

10:21.040 --> 10:23.680
OK, yeah, cool.
Where are we going?

10:24.520 --> 10:26.160
-I'm coming with you.

10:26.680 --> 10:28.360
What do we need?
Juice, snacks...

10:30.120 --> 10:31.120
Frodo!

10:31.400 --> 10:32.520
For energy.

10:34.920 --> 10:36.000
Frodo!

10:37.240 --> 10:39.240
-Not really.

10:39.320 --> 10:40.760
I do. From now.  Oh, come on, Frodo!

10:44.040 --> 10:46.000
I'm just gonna start the car.

10:47.800 --> 10:50.320
He's just hot-wiring. It takes a while.

10:50.880 --> 10:53.320
Oh, OK. Cool.

10:55.040 --> 10:56.320
Do you want some alcohol?

10:57.160 --> 10:58.360
Uh, yeah, sure.

10:59.840 --> 11:02.800
Can you grab us a couple
of bottles of that whiskey on top?

11:02.880 --> 11:05.240
This one?
-Yeah, the Glen-thingy one.

11:05.320 --> 11:08.240
It's really expensive.
Don't you dare!

11:08.720 --> 11:11.160
<i> His trust in us is</i>
<i>kind of heartbreaking.</i>

11:11.880 --> 11:13.800
<i>But what are you gonna do?</i>

11:16.520 --> 11:17.360
Hey!

11:18.880 --> 11:21.640
<i>♪ Well, Daddy joined the Air Force,</i>
<i>said it was a good source... ♪</i>

11:22.160 --> 11:23.840
Drive! Drive!

11:24.280 --> 11:25.680
Fucking drive!

11:27.560 --> 11:28.560
Wait!

11:29.560 --> 11:32.280
<i>♪ Here I am standin'</i>
<i>in the desert with a gun ♪</i>

11:32.360 --> 11:34.680
<i>♪ Thought of going AWOL</i>
<i>but I'm too afraid to run ♪</i>

11:34.760 --> 11:37.720
<i>♪ So I got me off of deep space</i>
<i>Help 'em win the arms race ♪</i>

11:37.800 --> 11:40.000
-Whoo!
-Woo-hoo!

11:41.360 --> 11:43.120
We're proper bandits, James!

11:46.000 --> 11:48.720
<i>♪ Threw me on a lily pad,</i>
<i>sent me home to NORAD ♪</i>

11:48.800 --> 11:51.880
<i>♪ I knew I'd be in trouble</i>
<i>but I didn't think it'd be this bad ♪</i>

12:02.040 --> 12:03.720
We're sorry to have to do this,

12:03.800 --> 12:05.960
but we just need
to ask some more questions.

12:07.680 --> 12:12.200
Going back a few years, there was talk
among old colleagues, about accusations

12:12.280 --> 12:14.080
made against Clive by some students.

12:14.720 --> 12:17.200
-Yes. I can tell you it was a long time ago...

12:21.080 --> 12:24.280
and that both accusations were dropped.

12:24.800 --> 12:27.760
-We know that, but--
-And I can tell you...

12:28.960 --> 12:31.600
that some young women,
rather than admit

12:31.680 --> 12:34.160
their grades are dropping
because they're lazy

12:34.240 --> 12:36.000
or on drugs half the time,

12:36.080 --> 12:40.520
would rather accuse
an innocent man of sexual assault.

12:41.320 --> 12:43.680
No one would have any reason
to cause him harm?

12:45.000 --> 12:46.160
I would like it...

12:47.040 --> 12:49.720
if you would get on with your job

12:49.800 --> 12:52.280
and find whoever murdered my son.

12:52.680 --> 12:56.160
Rather than trying to blame him
for his own death.

12:58.720 --> 12:59.720
I'll show you out.

13:00.240 --> 13:02.520
Please, we'll see ourselves out.

13:10.760 --> 13:11.840
He was your only one?

13:17.800 --> 13:20.560
It's better to be in charge of the truth,
you know?

13:21.800 --> 13:23.200
In case it ever comes out.

13:23.680 --> 13:24.840
It tends to,

13:24.920 --> 13:26.840
in situations like this. It's, uh...

13:27.440 --> 13:28.920
It's just my experience.

13:29.960 --> 13:31.800
It's better to be, you know...

13:33.280 --> 13:34.280
in control.

13:35.440 --> 13:36.960
Get out.

13:39.720 --> 13:41.200
I'm so sorry for your loss.

14:00.640 --> 14:02.440
<i> I think I'm starting</i>
<i>to feel a bit...</i> <i>more like myself.</i>

14:05.480 --> 14:09.280
<i>Sometimes, I think I feel more like myself</i>
<i>with James than I do on my own.</i>

14:10.440 --> 14:12.240
Hey, can you stop?

14:13.960 --> 14:16.040
<i> Everything feels really simple.</i>

14:47.160 --> 14:48.920
<i> Hello?</i>
Hi, Mum.

14:49.000 --> 14:51.280
<i>Oh, my God, Alyssa,</i>
<i>where the hell are you?</i>

14:51.360 --> 14:54.320
<i>-We've had the police around--</i>
-Just shut up and listen to me.

14:54.400 --> 14:56.040
<i>-Alyssa!</i>
-Mum.

14:57.040 --> 14:58.960
<i>Are you... are you OK?</i>

14:59.040 --> 15:01.840
You're never going to see me again. Ever.

15:01.920 --> 15:03.320
